title: Ghost is coming back in S8!
body:
“Oh, you’ll see him again. He has a fair amount of screen time in Season 8,” VFX supervisor Joe Bauer told me in an interview in August. “He does show up.” 

“Ghost does show up, and he does some … he’s very present and does some pretty cool things in Season 8,” he said.

summary: Why did all the mothers of t3HotD need to die in CHILDBIRTH? I get that it's thematically important for all 3 to experience...
question: Why did all the mothers of t3HotD need to die in CHILDBIRTH? I get that it's thematically important for all 3 to experience isolation and ostracism, but- fine, Lyanna's birth at 16 was always risky, Joanna's death has been a key pillar of the form Tyrion's abuse took, but Rhaella survived numerous pregnancies and stillbirths. Why not say she caught the same eating illness Ser Willam did, or they all did but while the children recovered the adults didn't.  Chicken pox does that in our world!
answer:
Yeah, that’s a decision of GRRM’s I’m not keen on. You’ve pointed out how Joanna’s death-in-childbirth shaped Tyrion’s abuse at Tywin’s hands, and I can defend in isolation Lyanna’s death-in-childbirth, since the timing of her death is a critical part of how Jon’s childhood was shaped and Ned’s own character development. But it’s not in isolation, and this is most noticeable in Dany’s case.

There’s nothing about Rhaella’s death in childbirth that could not have been accomplished by Rhaella’s death of pox, pneumonia, cancer, fall down the stairs, infected papercut, boating accident, lightning strike, falling meteorite, or choking on a fishbone, provided that incident took place when Dany couldn’t remember and Viserys was far too young to cope.
